Method Detail

add

public QueryBuilder add(Source<?>... sources)
Adds the given dimensions or metrics to the results from this query.

filter

public QueryBuilder filter(Filter filter)
Filters the data from this query through the given operation. If a filter is already set, it's and'd with the given filter. If the filters reference sources not currently in the query, those sources are added to the results.

sort

public QueryBuilder sort(Source<?>... sources)
Sorts the results from this query in ascending order by the given sources, in the order that the sources are given. If the query already contains sort sources, these sources are applied after the existing sources.

sortDescending

public QueryBuilder sortDescending(Source<?>... sources)
Sorts the results from this query in descending order by the given sources, in the order that the sources are given. If the query already contains sort sources, these sources are applied after the existing sources.

from

public QueryBuilder from(int year,
                         int month,
                         int day)
Sets the start day for the query to the specified day in the specified month and year.

Parameters:
year - a regular year value, like 1900
month - a 0-based month value, like Calendar.JANUARY
day - a regular day of the month value, like 31

startIndex

public QueryBuilder startIndex(int index)
Sets the index in the full set of results to start with for this particular query. Results start with index 1, and if no start index is supplied, the query goes from 1.

maxResults

public QueryBuilder maxResults(int max)
Sets the maximum number of results to return from a single query. The default is 1,000, and no more than 10,000 can be returned in a request.
